<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>bool anonymous&#95;namespace&#123;X86LowerAMXType.cpp&#125;::X86LowerAMXCast::optimizeAMXCastFromPhi (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/intrinsicinst">IntrinsicInst</a> &#42; CI, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/phinode">PHINode</a> &#42; PN, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallsetvector">SmallSetVector</a>&lt; <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/instruction">Instruction</a> &#42;, 16 &gt; &amp; DeadInst)</>}>
This function handles following case.

<CodeBlock>A  -&gt;  B    amxcast
PHI
B  -&gt;  A    amxcast
</CodeBlock>

All the related PHI nodes can be replaced by new PHI nodes with type A. The uses of <code>CI</code> can be changed to the new PHI node corresponding to <code>PN</code>.
